<subSubSection id="B79C897D7D422B6A26659B4E60A3322D" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="644D576D13B85495A5BE4F94320968F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4A3FCCC82611BCC822B4B356B7CB997" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Male 
<taxonomicName id="B2EB27C7CBED6FF41F089C701BDC186E" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="AFD9E0086205DD480EE06F060FC61490" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="751139E36793AAD7B42F2CA851CDF74B" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37317553DD09BCE22ACF029C858B3BED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. species by the unique morphology of the pedipalp median apophysis that has a very acute, basally pointed tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="28FF08F1D366737BE2DAB93B918CCDEE" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9C</figureCitation>
) (median apophysis generally rounded C-shaped in all other species). Female genitalia are probably most similar to those of S. 
<taxonomicName id="2954B1D1BFD113CBB2FD5A2BFF14562E" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Berland" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa canalae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="3323B368596C9A041A91EA31F1240FD7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., but the scape of 
<taxonomicName id="42A42FD5EFA68C676D43FA79DDB5FD41" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="5C1A1E2C4D329426EDEBD86987FD0A71" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is shorter than the epigyne plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ABA3E2F6AD1E4148A67BD7BAB6B6645B" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10C</figureCitation>
), whereas it is longer than the plate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C385F82504819254BD81BB9121A06C6" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="A0DAF82A46365A1EB85D0933707D0D8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DAF1A9B3FC9C09476107D7EA0B71D221" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19924395D1372F45E7CF932C31507665" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="4C1FD82D9283464EFA8A96BB9C67A379" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D173EDD226DB2ADBB92790D4E7B736F" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="2E3E35B098AFF917943B8EF15938CA2D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male</emphasis>
(based on NHMD 12231). Total length 4.4. Carapace 2.3 long, 1.9 wide, dark brown, slightly paler anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06C1DA9CCBA0D8496863E65E6B60A987" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.12, ALE 0.11, PME 0.14, PLE 0.09; row of eyes: AME 0.32, PME 0.33, PLE 0.90. Chelicerae pale brown; with three promarginal teeth (median largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs brown, femora basally yellow-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A9682831578FEDCD084A97304A4597EB" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9A, B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 2.5 + 1.1 + 2.0 + 1.6 + 0.7 = 7.9, II - 2.2 + 1.0 + 1.4 + 1.5 + 0.6 = 6.7, III - 1.4 + 0.6 + 0.7 + 0.7 + 0.5 = 3.9, IV - 2.0 + 0.7 + 1.3 + 1.4 + 0.6 = 6.0. Labium 0.27 long, 0.35 wide, brown; endites beige (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD8712E5FEEA535D4D02683A2C6A9D4C" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.1 long, 0.7 wide, dark brown with black radial shading (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92AB986C7CCD10AABD0A7F33DD816C29" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 2.1 long, 1.7 wide, posteriorly pointed; dorsum with beige background and large, irregular, olive-grey, folium, laterally pale olive-grey with black streaks (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4C430ED0CAB0338CEFF85255AF3566D2" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9A</figureCitation>
); venter dark grey, laterally with two elongate white bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AFB0453C6945DEDA29485AC47D525355" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="748794AC73D7A66ACBAD16FD7756BAA6" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">9C, D</figureCitation>
) length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + cymbium = total length): 0.3 + 0.2 + 0.1 + 0.65 = 1.25; paracymbium strong and curved apically; median apophysis transverse, terminating in an acute and basally pointed tip; denticles in basal arch of median apophysis distinct; conductor lobe narrow; terminal apophysis enlarged, sub-rectangular, bearing a reduced basal prong; conductor bilobed; embolus short, heavily sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73F4D2F024A81D045774C4FFF47321F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="F97E36BCF8218F3A9FE3DBDA528E8743" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on AM KS.131087): Total length 6.9. Carapace 3.0 long, 2.3 wide; dark brown, cephalic area paler (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C49D9FA9CBDB847AC49EB4D8C3C5CCA7" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.14, ALE 0.09, PME 0.07, PLE 0.07; row of eyes: AME 0.41, PME 0.38, PLE 1.35. Chelicerae orange-brown, four promarginal teeth (apical and second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth of similar size. Legs brown, patellae and tibiae apically slightly darker (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BFEC61712DC8C5CD45790477F97B07DC" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 0.9 + 0.5 + 0.5 + 1.0 = 2.9. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 2.4 + 1.1 + 1.8 + 1.9 + 0.9 = 8.1, II - 2.1 + 1.1 + 1.5 + 1.7 + 0.7 = 7.1, III - 1.2 + 0.7 + 0.8 + 0.8 + 0.5 = 4.0, IV - 2.1 + 1.0 + 1.4 + 1.5 + 0.6 = 6.6. Labium 0.36 long, 0.59 wide, dark brown; endites dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8FDBA5B88F0A580C3845BBDFCF12FDFE" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.3 long, 1.1 wide, orange-brown, with some paler discolourations (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A036B43135440D8B4183AB8B71B06D94" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 4.7 long, 4.6 wide; dorsum beige with olive-brown folium, laterally covered by orange-brown streaks (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="44DFF5009466117D71FFC85105C82B4F" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10A</figureCitation>
); venter olive-grey centrally with paler mottles, laterally with elongate white bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D7894D94324C159394C14408764D8019" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne base almost circular, slightly wider than long, with narrow elevated borders and therefore atrium extends almost over whole base (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="79678C6154A5989AC9EDC366ECA9A95A" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10C</figureCitation>
); scape slightly less than half of epigyne base, slightly wrinkled and its sides parallel (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="450AF4378107130E845ADAED6C06D69C" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS. 131087) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">10C</figureCitation>
); central division wide and abruptly tapering dorsally; spermathecae narrow pointing apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="49E29C214626B4FD210EA4E82D6681D9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Salsa gen. nov. female epigynes, cleared posterior view A S. fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov. (CVIC 173) B S. brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. (AM KS. 131087) C S. canalae comb. nov. Berland, 1924, comb. nov. (WAM T 75921) D S. recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. (WAM T 77362) E S. rueda sp. nov. F S. tartara sp. nov. (AM KS. 7061). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686604" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="411D7A5EEBD8AB6DBE5BD50791390AF1" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686608" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="A0274503DC76C69C58F4B2DFA59D8A37" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="14ED50002B06FDE651243280FDD382AF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F3814CAEE669E25C44285E900BC9BE9F" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa brisbanae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="D490D27D9CCD37E3F5BCF57B0B6E818F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., male (NHMD 12231) 
<emphasis id="DD058A4243D08365599D3F60F962A71C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
dorsal habitus 
<emphasis id="2D3B24FAFFE15FA23DB69CA22EE3462F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
ventral habitus 
<emphasis id="14E3446F8EB77D925AD537950839BB3E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
left pedipalp, ventral view 
<emphasis id="5728C91A38AC2692CF5DF2818E069E17" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">D</emphasis>
left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="C74D3992FAA8908DC24732B9B8616032" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A, B</emphasis>
); 0.2 mm (
<emphasis id="BCDF0D3371BCC056D9D95323A8D95215" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C, D</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5798ED3B3AA031672E22F1939E00AFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="variation">
<paragraph id="14526C1ED0326FE58263337052147204" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD1B2AB0A62340B8ACA88BC20D0EAA26" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Only one other male was measured, total length 3.9; females total lengths 6.9-7.9 (
<emphasis id="3CD727FD4E86B83AA640F23A96A42CB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">n</emphasis>
= 4). Like in other species of the genus, the colour variations in 
<taxonomicName id="60231F2F2EC6230FFBC260B4B74093F2" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="70B67D8B9F5BB8496469608488C0704A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. can be considerable and range from pale to dark brown tones in live specimens with the folium pattern on the abdomen more or less distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E4F6CCA03C6D09A6B19820E8978C1D14" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="life history and habitat preferences">
<paragraph id="C257C97B3BEB35FBFFEFC3BA41ED6D71" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Life history and habitat preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABBC884E0B910B307623DB4D6E19BB04" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Male and female specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="E871F11B9AF0CCA4E835071E552698E4" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="7A97B23581B15D7A84950DA6F6B88A2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. have mainly been found between October and May, with only few specimens collected from June to September. Although mature spiders can therefore be found all year round, the species should be considered as mainly late-summer to autumn mature. Most specimens were apparently collected on leaves and bark as labels indicate sweeping and beating as the main collection techniques that were used to capture the spiders.
</paragraph>
<caption id="846E1CB86F29B7B3867F389A5E0876FE" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686609" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 10" startId="F10">
<paragraph id="58552DA65865C67AE8A690E6309515C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="DC3EEA957174539D18E12FCE751571B8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="37452390D6BFCA768D79D4B1D6BFD281" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa brisbanae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="14492E7A68F08E808ADD23432FCE5060" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov., female (AM KS.131087) 
<emphasis id="FA192F3DBE25470E21A3228719BCD89D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
dorsal habitus 
<emphasis id="0FD00CFE1EC216DD7C1CCE38CFCB7109" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
ventral habitus 
<emphasis id="E0D6DCF03295B3B0B56BE02ADB05B5A1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
epigyne, ventral view 
<emphasis id="A7344787D287F24812B1FD46C9EDA114" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">D</emphasis>
epigyne, lateral view 
<emphasis id="73249F4CE2C1040FD3BE9723A055EBBE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">E</emphasis>
epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="7819D600D0583083FBB25B2CC156AD94" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A, B</emphasis>
); 0.2 mm (
<emphasis id="6E3E33C2AA780C7566788B8F2ECBFC94" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C-E</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6B8C2BE4CDE5BF22480666CF77BED5F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="5DF9A91B14E25966B10D12590A288FBC" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa brisbanae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="050EAF5E68EA235F336ACB0FB27D825B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. does not seem to be very habitat-specific, with specimens being collected in completely different environments, mostly in lower vegetation. Habitat descriptions on labels with specimens include 
<normalizedToken id="2B58B5ACC7FDDB6CE380A36D4BBF1048" originalValue="“rainforest”">&quot;rainforest&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="7D72B5818882CD69A964A958627F4BE8" originalValue="“shrubs”">&quot;shrubs&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="9F1766A277B529A2909093161B43AA0D" originalValue="“grass”">&quot;grass&quot;</normalizedToken>
, and 
<normalizedToken id="ADD10CB800C0E7030FE85FBD70629A31" originalValue="“foliage”">&quot;foliage&quot;</normalizedToken>
; but also 
<normalizedToken id="C2416B1974F201CB5EDA1E0902295C17" originalValue="“dune”">&quot;dune&quot;</normalizedToken>
and &quot;lagoon vegetation&quot;. Plant species that were cited at collection sites include 
<taxonomicName id="45F75BBC37B97F719347C53119634361" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acacia longifolia" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolia">
<emphasis id="FCF709DCE66A733D290882F0B5EE1DBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Acacia longifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(long-leaved wattle), 
<taxonomicName id="8F44FBAB4BBFB43D355A3260A2A90A89" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Leptospermum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leptospermum laevigatum" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis id="562E2C19DAF5BBCD4B80786848202785" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Leptospermum laevigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(coast tea tree), and 
<taxonomicName id="3CB1FD7D5DE8ADD1E4BF69612F4BC848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Monotoca" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monotoca elliptica" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliptica">
<emphasis id="85F0407D8378319D6D95656ABC36CA51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Monotoca elliptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(tree broom heath).
</paragraph>
<caption id="C2AF8C04B4C2D0681D035F0B8C6FA49A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686610" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 11" startId="F11">
<paragraph id="AC21F9B91A5F5120E043208CD5E6C358" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="27992B80B08453D9761E5A699F5CF0FD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 11.</emphasis>
Distribution records of 
<taxonomicName id="A903EEFC04E1A339EA184A544166AD10" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa brisbanae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="E9B954917F6025678C1F7D49BC208B9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="97F6F9226D49EAB6F38C0B94484F42CD" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Main" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa recherchensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="51B8F25387FFA5BD15A2EF69924E5AE6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Main, 1954), comb. nov. in Australia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C6C3FDCAE77F338151A87C71F946D2DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2F2A10E6CA413AD4E85E64B043901D65" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E1EFE111967165A498244F6B95BB851" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="483120B5151CB663B598E470FCD7EB32" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa brisbanae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="0A29DAED53BCF10BBED42090A1874DE0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. occurs in Queensland, New South Wales, Victoria and Tasmania (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CC6B959CF079A9A423CDB2EEEE630A03" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution records of Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. and Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. in Australia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686610" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">11</figureCitation>
). The species was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="ABB8A0F2C878D78FB1068FC773433F70" author="Keyserling, E" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" refId="B23" refString="Keyserling, E, 1887. Die Arachniden Australiens nach der Natur beschrieben und abgebildet. 2. Theil. 3. Lieferung. Bauer &amp; Raspe, Nuernberg, 153-232." title="Die Arachniden Australiens nach der Natur beschrieben und abgebildet. 2. Theil. 3. Lieferung. Bauer &amp; Raspe, Nuernberg, 153 - 232." year="1887">Keyserling (1887)</bibRefCitation>
from New Zealand (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="B6A1A7C1611BBA248E8DE8FF9DE412D7" author="Dalmas, Rd" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="317 - 430" refId="B9" refString="Dalmas, Rd, 1917. Aragnees de Nouvelle Zelande. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 86: 317 - 430" title="Aragnees de Nouvelle Zelande." volume="86" year="1917">Dalmas 1917</bibRefCitation>
), but this record is likely based on a misidentification (
<bibRefCitation id="88586F2FC315699B59A2DA88B11F385D" author="Paquin, P" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Mundi" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 6" publicationUrl="https://digitalcommons.unl.edu/insectamundi/574/" refId="B29" refString="Paquin, P, Vink, CJ, Duperre, N, Sirvid, P, Court, DJ, 2008. Nomina dubia and faunistic issues with New Zealand spiders (Araneae). Insecta Mundi 46: 1 - 6, https://digitalcommons.unl.edu/insectamundi/574/" title="Nomina dubia and faunistic issues with New Zealand spiders (Araneae)." url="https://digitalcommons.unl.edu/insectamundi/574/" volume="46" year="2008">Paquin et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The species was apparently also recorded from Papua New Guinea (
<bibRefCitation id="77E09EDECE708E8A5E6D8DD3FD6BC16E" author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B36" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2022. . Version 23.0. http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title=". Version 23.0." url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2022">World Spider Catalog 2022</bibRefCitation>
), but we could not find any original citation that suggests this distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
